Jaimie Ding reports: Attorney General Rob Bonta filed the lawsuit against Chrome Holding Co., which 23andMe rebranded under after filing for bankruptcy last March. 23andme is known for its direct-to-consumer DNA test kits that provided customers information on their ancestry and genetic predispositions for certain health conditions. The lawsuit calls for various civil penalties against 23andMe...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F05%2F29%2Fcalifornia-ag-bonta-sues-chrome-holding-co-formerly-known-as-23andme-over-2023-data-breach%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dcalifornia-ag-bonta-sues-chrome-holding-co-formerly-known-as-23andme-over-2023-data-breach&amp;action_name=California%20AG%20Bonta%20Sues%20Chrome%20Holding%20Co.%2C%20Formerly%20Known%20as%2023andMe%2C%20Over%202023%20Data%20Breach&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
<p><a href="https://databreaches.net/2026/05/29/california-ag-bonta-sues-chrome-holding-co-formerly-known-as-23andme-over-2023-data-breach/?pk_campaign=feed&#038;pk_kwd=california-ag-bonta-sues-chrome-holding-co-formerly-known-as-23andme-over-2023-data-breach">Source</a></p>

